I'm surprised to find relatively few pizza spots around Columbia. For its many deficits NYU at least has a bubble of good and cheap pizza.  The paucity of competition means high prices and mediocre quality. I paid $4.25 for one of those mozzarella and tomato slices, and it wasn't particularly large, and nor was it particularly tasty.  The atmosphere is decent, with okay air conditioning and lots and lots of chairs and tables.  They have a really nice bathroom.. pretty clean, very well air-conditioned, and with actual running water (not a trickle). So there's that.

A really decent slice even though they are a chain. Thin crust good sauce and cheese and grease that drips on your wrist. Nice cheese/sauce/dough ratio. Their slices are small though for the inflated price. You might do better a few blocks away at Koronet where you can get a giant slice for $3.75!

Crowd: 20-30s Mostly Columbia students & faculty. Service: Quick and courteous.
